Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.69,0:00:26.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}成为宇宙公民的梦想\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The dream of becoming a citizen of the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.89,0:00:31.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在2000年前 诞生于此\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was born here, more than two millennia ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.16,0:00:33.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}亚历山大城\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the city of Alexandria,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.40,0:00:36.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这座城市的名字是为了纪念它的征服者\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}named after and conceived by its dead conqueror,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.67,0:00:38.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}已去世的亚历山大大帝\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Alexander the Great.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.62,0:00:40.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}希腊的托勒密王朝\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Ptolemys, the Greek kings
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.65,0:00:43.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}继承了亚历山大帝国的埃及地区\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who inherited the Egyptian portion of Alexander's empire,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:43.65,0:00:45.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并修建了这座图书馆\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}built this library
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.72,0:00:48.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}成立了相关的研究机构\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its associated research institution.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.73,0:00:50.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以说 这是非常罕见的举措\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rarely, if ever,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.36,0:00:52.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不仅空前 而且绝后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before or since,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.06,0:00:54.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从没有一个政府会花那么多钱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has there been a government that was willing to spend
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.67,0:00:56.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把国家收入的大部分\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so much of its gross national product
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.90,0:00:59.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}投入到对知识的获取中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the acquisition of knowledge.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.40,0:01:00.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有付出就有回报\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And it paid off.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.84,0:01:02.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}知识的大时代来临了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Big time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.34,0:01:05.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一艘进入亚历山大港的船只\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Every ship entering Alexandria's harbor
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.58,0:01:08.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都要进行搜查 查的不是违禁品\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was searched-- not for contraband,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.48,0:01:11.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而是那些放在船上的书籍手抄本\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but for books that might be copied and stored here,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.25,0:01:15.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发现后就归入这座当时世界上最伟大的图书馆\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in what was then the greatest library on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.09,0:01:24.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}正是在这里 图书馆的馆长埃拉托斯特尼\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here, Eratosthenes, one of the chief librarians,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.66,0:01:27.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}准确的计算出了地球的直径\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}accurately calculated the size of the Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.83,0:01:29.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并创建了地理学\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and invented geography.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.44,0:01:33.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}毕达哥拉斯\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pythagoras.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:34.77,0:01:37.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}希帕蒂娅\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hypatia.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.34,0:01:40.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}欧几里得\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Euclid.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.75,0:01:47.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}欧几里得在著作中阐述了几何学的定律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Euclid set forth the precepts of geometry
Dialogue: 0,0:01:47.38,0:01:51.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}2300年后 他的著作依然被世人使用\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a textbook that remained in use for 2,300 years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.36,0:02:00.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}《圣经?旧约》也是从这里开始散播到人世\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Old Testament Bible comes down to us
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.36,0:02:02.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}经书的大部分在这里被翻译成了希腊语\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}mainly from the Greek translations made here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.77,0:02:05.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}很多伟大作品的原始手稿也保存在这里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The original manuscripts of the masterpieces
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.87,0:02:08.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}包括希腊的喜剧 戏剧 诗歌\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of Greek comedy and drama, poetry,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.37,0:02:10.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学著作 工程著作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}science, engineering,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.77,0:02:13.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}医学著作 历史著作\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}medicine and history--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.54,0:02:15.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}失落的古代文明作品被重新唤醒\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the total work product
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.41,0:02:18.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}妥妥的保存在这里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the awakening of ancient civilization-- were kept here.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.45,0:02:21.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}据推测 这里的藏书\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Estimates vary on the total number of scrolls.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.89,0:02:25.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大概有50万卷以上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They range from 500,000
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.06,0:02:27.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}甚至多达上百万卷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to nearly a million.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.66,0:02:29.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所有的这些作品\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And all of it...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.63,0:02:31.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所有的这些书籍\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all of this
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.10,0:02:33.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在只需要很小的一个空间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is but a tiny fraction of the information
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.40,0:02:37.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像你的指尖那么大的地方就可以保存了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that you have at your fingertips at this very moment.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.74,0:02:43.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类集体的知识\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The collective knowledge of our species,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.07,0:02:46.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}存在我们自己的亚历山大电子图书馆里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our own electronic Library of Alexandria,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.34,0:02:49.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只要你身上带有相应的设备 就随时可以获取\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}may be accessed by anyone who has a device
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.45,0:02:52.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你爱看什么就看什么 什么时候想看就什么时候看\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the interest and the freedom to do so.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.35,0:02:54.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可在过去的亚历山大城 这样的事情是不会发生的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This was not true in Alexandria,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.82,0:02:56.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}知识只属于某些精英人士\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where knowledge belonged to the elite.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.92,0:02:59.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此在公元前四世纪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So in the fourth century AD,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.59,0:03:02.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当暴民摧毁图书馆时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when the mob came to destroy the library
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.43,0:03:04.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当古典文明的精华被摧毁时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the genius of classical civilization,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.86,0:03:08.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有什么人站起来保卫它们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there were not enough people to defend it.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.33,0:03:12.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}等下一次的暴乱来临时 又会发生些什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What will happen the next time the mob comes?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.50,0:04:47.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\fe134}{\fsp0}{\fad(500,500)}{\pos(190,278)}{\fn方正准圆简体}{\bord0}{\fs20}{\c&H24EFFF&}宇宙大探索\n{\fs17}{\c&HFFFFFF&} 第十三集
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.64,0:04:54.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们已经一起经历了一段漫长的旅程\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We've come a long way together,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.97,0:04:58.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们深入了原子的内核\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}traveling from deep inside the heart of an atom
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.28,0:05:00.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}抵达了宇宙的边缘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}clear out to the cosmic horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.98,0:05:04.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从时间的起源走到遥远的未来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and from the beginning of time to the distant future.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.82,0:05:07.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们是时候做一些实验了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I think we're ready to perform an experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.94,0:05:37.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这不是那种在实验室里才能做的实验\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not the kind of experiment that requires a laboratory.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.25,0:05:39.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你可以在自己的脑海里完成它\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can do it in your head.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.32,0:05:41.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它称之为"思想实验"\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's called a "thought experiment."
Dialogue: 0,0:05:42.92,0:05:44.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}选一颗星星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pick a star--
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.79,0:05:47.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就在我们的银河系里选上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}any one of the hundreds of billions of stars
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.63,0:05:49.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这数以百亿颗星星中的一颗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in our Milky Way Galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.93,0:05:51.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其实银河系也只不过是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which is just one galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.76,0:05:54.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}目前已知宇宙的上百亿个星系中的一个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}out of the hundred billion in the known universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.00,0:05:56.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这颗怎么样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How about that star?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.63,0:05:58.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}或者是那一颗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Or that one?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.44,0:06:00.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}好 就是这颗吧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Okay, this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.54,0:06:03.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有几十个行星和卫星围绕着它旋转\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's orbited by dozens of planets and moons.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.87,0:06:05.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}假设 其中的一颗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Suppose, on one of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.94,0:06:07.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上面有智能生物存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there lives an intelligent species,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.01,0:06:12.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们是这个行星里上千万种生命形式的一种\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one the ten million life-forms on that planet,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:12.35,0:06:14.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这些智能生物中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and there's a subgroup of that species
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.49,0:06:17.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有一小部分生物认为他们已经发现了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who believe they have it all figured out--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.29,0:06:20.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个世界就是宇宙的中心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}their world is the center of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.46,0:06:23.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这个宇宙为他们而造\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a universe made for them,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.16,0:06:26.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们已经无所不知\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that they know everything they need to know about it--
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.50,0:06:29.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}拥有了圆满的智慧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}their knowledge is complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.47,0:06:32.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你觉得他们的话可以当真吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How seriously would you take their claim?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.04,0:06:40.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的祖先就认为\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our ancestors believed
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.08,0:06:42.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙是为他们而造的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the universe was made for them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.21,0:06:44.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把人假定为世界的中心是很自然的事情\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was natural to assume that we were at the center.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:44.98,0:06:47.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}毕竟 太阳和其它的星星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After all, it looks like the Sun and stars
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.35,0:06:49.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}看起来都围绕着人类转\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all revolve around us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.42,0:06:52.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们现在还在说 太阳是"升"起来的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We still speak of the Sun "rising."
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.49,0:06:55.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类的语言 神话和梦想的体系结构\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The architecture of our language, myths and dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.36,0:06:58.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是来自科学诞生前的时代\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}comes from that pre-scientific age.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.70,0:07:02.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在哥伦布出航发现新大陆前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This is our planet as it was known then,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.07,0:07:04.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人们都认为已经很了解这个星球了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}just before Columbus set sail.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.74,0:07:07.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是世界上第一个地球仪\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This first globe of the Earth was cutting-edge
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.51,0:07:10.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}马丁?贝海姆在1492年制造了这个当时是最前沿的产品\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when Martin Behaim made it in 1492.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.71,0:07:13.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和当时的其它人一样 他认为\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like everyone else, he believed
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.24,0:07:16.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这幅世界地理的拼图已经完整无缺了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that the jigsaw puzzle of geography was complete.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.88,0:07:18.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}上面有三个大陆\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There were three continents...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.75,0:07:20.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}欧洲 非洲和亚洲\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Europe, Africa and Asia,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.02,0:07:23.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}三个大洲之间只有浩瀚的大洋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and only the great world ocean in between.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.72,0:07:28.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}贝海姆地球仪上看不到北美洲与南美洲的存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Behaim had no clue that North and South America even existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:30.46,0:07:33.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人很容易自以为是 对不对\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's easy to feel smug, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.90,0:07:38.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}事实上 马丁?贝海姆对他的世界的了解\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, the fact is Martin Behaim knew infinitely more
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.70,0:07:40.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对地球的了解\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about his world, the Earth,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.81,0:07:44.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}远远胜过我们对于宇宙的了解\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than we know about ours, the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.98,0:07:47.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}近代有一个关于谦虚的故事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A recent lesson in humility
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.04,0:07:50.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可以很好的作为明证\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will serve to illustrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.25,0:07:54.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1912年 维克托?赫斯进行了好几次飞行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1912, Victor Hess made a series of voyages
Dialogue: 0,0:07:54.92,0:07:56.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他飞越了奥地利上空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the sky above Austria,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.79,0:07:59.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发现了科学家们期待已久的东西…\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and found the thing that scientists love best...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.59,0:08:04.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一个神秘而无法理解的事件\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a mystery that defied understanding
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.26,0:08:07.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}用传统的科学无法解释\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in terms of conventional scientific wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.63,0:08:10.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时至今日\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And even today,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.47,0:08:13.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}100年过去了 我们仍在苦苦搜寻\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a century later, we are still searching
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.77,0:08:16.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要为赫斯的发现找一个完整的答案\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a complete explanation of what Hess found.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:18.48,0:08:21.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当时有一种新的能量刚被发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A new kind of energy had recently been discovered,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.58,0:08:22.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}辐射能\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}radioactivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.58,0:08:22.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\an8}{\fnMicrosoft JhengHei UI\fs18\b1\bord1\shad1\3c&H2F2F2F&}也就是放射能
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.98,0:08:24.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}自然界中某种特定的元素会释放出辐射\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was given off
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.45,0:08:26.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比如镭\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by certain elements, like radium.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.58,0:08:29.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但空气中也有辐射\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But it was also found in the air,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.29,0:08:32.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在远离放射性岩石的地方也有辐射\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}even far away from radioactive rocks.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.09,0:08:34.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它可说是无处不在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was everywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.76,0:08:37.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些奇怪的能量是从哪里来的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Where did this strange energy come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.33,0:08:39.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}无人知晓\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No one knew.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.66,0:08:43.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}赫斯推测它可能来自地球上空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hess suspected that it might come from above the Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.33,0:08:46.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为了验证这个假设 他携带着辐射探测器\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To test his hypothesis, he carried radiation detectors
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.30,0:08:47.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}飞向高空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}high into the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.97,0:08:51.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他冒着乘坐氢气球的风险\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}During a risky ascent in a hydrogen balloon,
