Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.45,0:08:58.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当他来到空气稀薄 温度寒冷的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When he reached the thin, cold,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.38,0:09:00.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大气层中部以上时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}upper half of the atmosphere...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.80,0:09:12.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他发现这里的辐射值\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he found that the radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:12.53,0:09:15.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比地面的要强2倍以上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was more than twice as strong as on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.70,0:09:19.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些辐射一定是来自于更高处\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The radiation must be coming from above.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.24,0:09:22.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此它在地面才会比较弱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's why its intensity was weaker on the ground--
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.37,0:09:25.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为地球的大气层吸收了大部分能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Earth's atmosphere was absorbing most of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.18,0:09:29.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有人认为这些辐射可能来自于太阳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some thought that the radiation might come from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.65,0:09:33.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为了测试这个说法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To test that idea, Hess timed one of his ascents
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.32,0:09:35.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}赫斯在一次日食时升上高空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to coincide with a solar eclipse.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.03,0:09:46.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他发现日食对辐射没有任何影响\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But the eclipse had no effect on the radiation.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.03,0:09:49.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}赫斯还发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hess also found that the radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.20,0:09:52.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}辐射在白天和晚上的强度是一样的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was just as strong at night as in daylight.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.67,0:09:55.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些辐射是来自于高空 但不是太阳\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was coming from above, but not from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.34,0:09:58.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}赫斯不知道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What Hess did not know
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.21,0:10:01.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳风根本就没有那么快的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was that the solar wind doesn't move that quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.38,0:10:03.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此 他凭着这个错误的理由\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And so, for the wrong reason,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.68,0:10:06.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}做出了正确的结论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he came to the right conclusion.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.88,0:10:09.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}赫斯发现了宇宙射线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hess had discovered cosmic rays--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.95,0:10:13.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那些如阵雨一般在宇宙中交错飞洒的亚原子粒子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}showers of subatomic particles that crisscross the universe
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.79,0:10:16.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们以光速行进着\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at literally the speed of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:16.19,0:10:18.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果没有地球大气层的保护\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Without the shielding effect of the Earth's atmosphere,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.80,0:10:20.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们可致人死地\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they would be lethal.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:20.80,0:10:23.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}某些宇宙射线携带的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some cosmic rays can carry as much energy
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.57,0:10:25.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与步枪中发射的子弹一样强\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as a bullet fired from a rifle.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.94,0:10:29.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类花了几十年的时间追踪宇宙射线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It would take decades to trace those cosmic rays
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.07,0:10:33.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}才发现它们那无法想象的恐怖死亡之面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}back to a death of unimaginable violence.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.64,0:10:47.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}赫斯在奥地利上空发现的宇宙射线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The cosmic rays that Victor Hess detected
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.67,0:10:51.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}向科学家们提出了一个谜\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the skies above Austria posed a mystery to scientists.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.90,0:10:56.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上的放射性矿物质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Radioactivity in minerals on Earth--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.20,0:10:58.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比如铀\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}like uranium ore--
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.57,0:11:01.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们的放射性来自于原子的裂变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}comes from the disintegration of atoms.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.10,0:11:04.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但宇宙射线具有不同的性质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But cosmic rays were of a different nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.27,0:11:06.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们的能量更强大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They were far more powerful
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.74,0:11:09.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}比当时赫斯的世界中任何一种已知物质都要强\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than anything known in Hess's world.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.25,0:11:11.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学家们探索了20年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Scientists wondered for two decades
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.42,0:11:14.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想要知道是什么东西产生了宇宙射线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what could possibly produce cosmic rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.08,0:11:17.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}下面介绍弗里茨?兹威基\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Enter Fritz Zwicky,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.69,0:11:21.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一个你从没听说过的最聪明的人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the most brilliant man you've never heard of.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.79,0:11:24.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1933年 他和一个同事发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In 1933, he and a colleague discovered
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.86,0:11:27.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}某些恒星会突然变得非常耀眼\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that some stars flare up to become as bright
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.63,0:11:29.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}亮度就和它们所在的星系差不多并延续好几周\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as their entire galaxy for a few weeks,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.87,0:11:32.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后又会黯淡下来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before fading out again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.30,0:11:33.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}弗里茨?兹威基是世界上第一个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Fritz Zwicky was the first person
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.80,0:11:36.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}了解这个现象的人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to understand what just happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.37,0:11:39.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他正确的推测出\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He correctly surmised that this is the way
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.38,0:11:41.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这代表着一颗大质量恒星的死亡\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a massive star dies-- it blows
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.58,0:11:43.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爆炸将恒星的物质抛入太空\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its guts out into space.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.65,0:11:47.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他把这种恒星的死亡称为"超新星"\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He called this kind of stellar death a "supernova"...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.42,0:11:55.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并推测这颗垂死的恒星将会坍缩\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and predicted that the dying star would shrink
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.13,0:11:57.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从100万英里的直径收缩为10英里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from about a million miles across to only ten.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.66,0:12:01.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}恒星的残骸密度如此之大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This corpse would be so dense
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.53,0:12:04.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一粒米那么大的物质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that a single grain of it would weigh as much
