Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.18,0:12:53.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在穿过这个星系时发生扭曲并放大的效应\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from any other galaxy lying directly behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.62,0:12:57.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此地球上的天文学家们在观测 具有相同距离的遥远星系时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So, astronomers on Earth would see multiple images
Dialogue: 0,0:12:57.25,0:12:59.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}会看到有多重图像出现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of that same distant galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.52,0:13:02.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就好像游乐园的哈哈镜效果\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}deformed, as in a funhouse mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.53,0:13:08.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他做出这一预测40年后 人们才开始发现这一现象真实存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}40 years after this prediction, we started finding them, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.97,0:13:13.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}兹威基在1930年代还有另一个发现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And Zwicky made yet another discovery back in the 1930s.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.00,0:13:17.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在观测后发座星系团时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}While studying the Coma Cluster of galaxies,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.54,0:13:22.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他注意到星团的移动方式很有意思\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}he noticed something funny about the way they moved.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.05,0:13:25.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的移动速度很快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The galaxies were going way too fast,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.28,0:13:28.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这么快的速度下 这个星团早就该飞散了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so fast that they should've been flying apart from each other,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.45,0:13:30.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为在所有这些星系中的恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because all the stars in all those galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.89,0:13:34.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们的引力太小 无法维系整个星团的稳定\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}had far too little gravity to hold the cluster together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.33,0:13:36.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}兹威基认为\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Zwicky thought
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.13,0:13:38.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一定有某种力量将它们维系在一起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that something else must be binding them to each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.73,0:13:41.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这看不见找不着的神秘部分\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That mysterious missing component
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.57,0:13:44.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的重量至少是星团中所有的恒星总重的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would have to weigh something like 50 times as much
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.87,0:13:46.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}50倍以上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the stars themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.50,0:13:49.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但没人对他的超前见解感兴趣\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But no one paid much attention to this wild notion.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.81,0:13:52.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}认为那不过是兹威基的又一个疯狂的想法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Just another one of Zwicky's crazy ideas.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.01,0:13:54.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在我们的太阳系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In our solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.68,0:13:57.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}位于内圈的行星水星 它的移动速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the innermost planet, Mercury, moves much faster
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.25,0:13:59.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要比最外圈的行星海王星快许多\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than the outermost one, Neptune.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.25,0:14:01.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}听上去这很顺理成章 对不\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that makes sense, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.09,0:14:04.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你越是用力推拉一个物体 它的速度也就越快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The harder you push or pull on something, the faster it goes.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.49,0:14:07.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳的引力随距离的增加而会减弱\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun's gravity weakens with increasing distance,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.83,0:14:12.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此 距离太阳更远的行星移动得更慢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so, the planets that are farther from the Sun move more slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.23,0:14:15.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人们认为星系最外层的恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Everyone expected that the outermost stars in a galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.93,0:14:18.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也应该是这样移动的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}would act the same way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.60,0:14:22.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大部分的恒星都向着星系的中心集中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the stars are concentrated towards the center,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.11,0:14:25.38,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此 它们的重力总和会牵引其它的恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so, their collective gravity pulls on the other stars
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.41,0:14:28.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如同太阳牵引行星一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the same way the Sun pulls on the planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.61,0:14:31.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可是在1970年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But in the 1970s, when astronomer
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.05,0:14:33.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}天文学家维拉・鲁宾在研究M女座星系时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Vera Rubin studied the Andromeda Galaxy,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.45,0:14:37.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}她发现这个星系的外层恒星并没有遵循这个规律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}she discovered that the outer stars obeyed no such rule.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.02,0:14:40.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们与太阳系的外层行星不一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Unlike the outer planets of the solar system,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.62,0:14:44.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星系外层恒星的速度\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the outer stars in the galaxy were all going at the same speed
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.36,0:14:46.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与星系内层恒星的速度是一样的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the stars that were closer in,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.70,0:14:49.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们移动得甚至比人们预想中的还要快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and they were moving way faster than expected.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.37,0:14:51.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}"太有意思了" 维拉想道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"That's funny," Vera thought.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.77,0:14:55.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}"M女座星系里一定有古怪"\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"There must be something weird about the Andromeda Galaxy."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.81,0:14:57.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}于是 她又观测另一个星系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So she looked at another galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.21,0:14:59.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发现了同样的现象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Same story.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.44,0:15:00.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}再下一个 也是如此\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And another.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.81,0:15:03.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}维拉一共观测了60个星系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Vera studied 60 galaxies
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.31,0:15:05.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发现所有的星系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and found that all of them
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.32,0:15:07.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}似乎都违背了万有引力定律\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}seemed to be violating the Law of Gravity,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.05,0:15:09.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是物理学中的核心理论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a core principle of physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.05,0:15:12.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一开始 她的同事们对这个现象表示质疑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}After some initial healthy skepticism,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.42,0:15:14.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}随后他们开始动手自己观测\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}her colleagues looked for themselves,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.46,0:15:17.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}结果发现维拉的观测结果是正确的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and found that Vera was right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.76,0:15:20.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但并非是牛顿的万有引力定律有问题\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's not that Isaac Newton had gotten the Law of Gravity wrong;
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.93,0:15:23.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而是维拉・鲁宾发现了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Vera Rubin had discovered that the gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.50,0:15:25.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}某种巨大而又不可见的引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of something massive and invisible
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.60,0:15:29.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在迫使星星们移动加快\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was forcing the stars to go fast.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.84,0:15:35.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}然后 有人想起了疯狂的老兹威基的说法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And then, someone remembered crazy old Fritz Zwicky,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.35,0:15:38.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那不明来源的引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the unknown source of gravity
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.32,0:15:39.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}肯定是存在于星系团中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the galaxy clusters
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.85,0:15:43.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1933年的时候 他就将其称之为"暗物质"\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that he called "dark matter," back in 1933.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.16,0:15:52.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}维拉・鲁宾证实了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Vera Rubin had verified the existence
