Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.43,0:20:38.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙的膨胀不仅没有减缓\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The expansion isn't slowing down at all...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.83,0:20:40.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而且还在不停的加速\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's speeding up.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.60,0:20:44.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这意味着宇宙会永远膨胀下去\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This means the universe will continue to expand forever.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.24,0:20:48.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙中似乎有一股神秘的力量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There seems to be a mysterious force in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.04,0:20:51.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的规模庞大得足以压倒一切引力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}one that overwhelms gravity on the grandest scale
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.04,0:20:53.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}将宇宙分开\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to push the cosmos apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.61,0:20:56.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙中大部分的能量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of the energy of the universe is bound up
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.35,0:20:57.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都被这股看不见的力量束缚着\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in this unknown force.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.85,0:21:00.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们称之为"暗能量"\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We call it "dark energy,"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.25,0:21:02.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}可这个名字就和"暗物质"一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but that name, like "dark matter,"
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.96,0:21:06.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们不知道它是什么 只能强给它起个名字而已\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is merely a code word for our ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.43,0:21:08.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们承认不知道所有问题的答案\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's okay not to know all the answers.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.80,0:21:10.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}承认自己的无知\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's better to admit our ignorance
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.80,0:21:13.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}总比强行认可那些可能错误的答案好\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than to believe answers that might be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:13.20,0:21:16.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}假装自己什么都懂 就是关上了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pretending to know everything closes the door
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.70,0:21:18.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}通往真相的大门\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to finding out what's really there.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.74,0:21:22.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}今晚 我们的飞船航行到了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Tonight, our ships sail
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.28,0:21:25.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}更奇异的水域\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into even more exotic waters.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.24,0:21:27.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}跟我来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.62,0:21:39.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类只有两艘飞船冒险进入了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Only two of our ships have ventured
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.92,0:21:43.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星际空间中的黑暗大洋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into the great dark ocean of interstellar space.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.43,0:21:47.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是史上最长的冒险之旅\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The longest odyssey in all of history
Dialogue: 0,0:21:47.30,0:21:50.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它开始于1977年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was launched back in 1977--
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.60,0:21:54.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}美国宇航局的旅行者1号与旅行者2号\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}NASA's Voyager 1 and 2.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.34,0:21:58.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这两艘飞船以每小时4万英里的速度行进\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Voyagers move about 40,000 miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.68,0:22:01.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们让人类得以第一次近距离观察\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They gave us our first close-up look
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.51,0:22:03.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}木星上的大红斑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at Jupiter's Great Red Spot,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.58,0:22:07.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是比地球的尺寸还要大三倍的飓风\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a hurricane three times the size of Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.49,0:22:11.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}其中一个飓风至少在1644年就已经开始刮起\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and one that's been raging since at least 1644,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.46,0:22:13.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并第一次被人类观测到\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}when it was first observed.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.19,0:22:16.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所以我们知道 这些飓风至少可以延续数千年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}For all we know, it could be thousands of years old.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.99,0:22:20.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旅行者号还发现了 在木星的卫星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Voyagers discovered the first active volcano
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.33,0:22:24.27,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}木卫一上有活火山的存在\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on another world, on Jupiter's moon Io...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.84,0:22:27.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在木卫二的冰层下\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and an ocean beneath the icy surface
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.01,0:22:29.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}则存在着海洋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the moon Europa...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.31,0:22:36.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它可能拥有比地球至少多2倍的液态水\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with at least twice as much water as we have here on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.95,0:22:43.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旅行者号还勇敢的飞越了土星环\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Voyagers dared to fly across Saturn's rings
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.35,0:22:47.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发现它是由数以百计的圆环带组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and revealed that they were made of hundreds of thin bands
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.73,0:22:49.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而这些圆环带则是由小雪球组成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of orbiting snowballs.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.90,0:22:55.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在土星的巨大卫星土卫六上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On Saturn's giant moon Titan,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.57,0:22:59.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旅行者号发现了比地球浓厚4倍的大气层\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Voyager detected an atmosphere four times denser than Earth's.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.74,0:23:04.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}暗示着在土卫六上有可能存在甲烷的海洋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That hinted at the existence of hydrocarbon seas on Titan,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.51,0:23:06.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这一点后来被证实了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}which we later confirmed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.15,0:23:10.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旅行者2号让人类第一次得到了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Voyager 2 gave us our first portrait
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.15,0:23:13.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最外层的行星 海王星的肖像\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the outermost planet, Neptune...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.99,0:23:17.85,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}海王星上狂风咆哮 风速达每小时1000英里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where the winds roar at 1,000 miles per hour...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.69,0:23:22.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在它的卫星海卫一上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and its moon Triton, where geysers
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.59,0:23:27.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}间歇泉能把沸腾的液氮喷到5英里高\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of boiling nitrogen shoot five miles high.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:30.23,0:23:33.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旅行者号成功的完成了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Voyager successfully completed its mission of discovery
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.07,0:23:34.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它对外层行星的观测任务\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the outer planets,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.91,0:23:36.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但它进入黑暗世界的冒险之旅\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but its odyssey into the darkness
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.91,0:23:38.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}才刚刚开始\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}was just beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.21,0:23:42.91,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在发射后的35年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}35 years after its launch,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.95,0:23:45.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旅行者1号成为人类第一个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Voyager 1 became the first of our spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.62,0:23:48.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}进入未知领域的太空飞船\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to enter an uncharted realm.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:48.52,0:23:51.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳向各个方向不断地发射出\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun is constantly shooting out streams
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.76,0:23:54.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}带电的粒子流\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of charged particles in all directions,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.09,0:23:56.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}粒子流的时速达100万英里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}moving at a million miles an hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:56.43,0:24:01.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是太阳风 它扩散后的区域是一个巨大的磁泡\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This solar wind blows a vast magnetic bubble,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.20,0:24:05.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}形成了太阳风层 它一直延伸到最外层的行星之外\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our heliosphere, that extends beyond the outer planets.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.10,0:24:10.44,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它把从星际空间进入的稀薄气体向外推\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It pushes out against the thin gas of interstellar space.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.47,0:24:15.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是一个世界的尽头 另一个世界的起点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There's a border where one ends and the other begins.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.08,0:24:17.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旅行者1号向地球报告说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Voyager 1 reported back to Earth
Dialogue: 0,0:24:17.25,0:24:19.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的探测器正在遭遇\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that its detectors were being pummeled
Dialogue: 0,0:24:19.78,0:24:21.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}越来越多的宇宙射线攻击\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by more and more cosmic rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.32,0:24:23.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}直至现在 我们还是不知道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Until then, we didn't know
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.75,0:24:26.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哪里才是浩瀚星际大洋的开始\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where the interstellar ocean began.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.36,0:24:28.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旅行者1号不断前行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Voyager 1 pressed on
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.63,0:24:31.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它穿越了人类从未穿越的边界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}past a boundary we had never crossed before.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.86,0:24:35.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳风层为我们阻挡了大部分致命的宇宙射线\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The heliosphere shields us from most of the deadly cosmic rays.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.73,0:24:37.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当太阳风如骤雨般爆发时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When stormy solar winds blow,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.90,0:24:40.10,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳风层也会随之扩张\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}this zone of protection grows;
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.14,0:24:42.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳风平静时 它会缩小\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in calm solar weather, it shrinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.27,0:24:45.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当银河系附近出现超新星爆发时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}When a star goes supernova in our galactic neighborhood...
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.38,0:24:49.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}爆发后的星体残骸\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the debris from the exploded star
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.65,0:24:52.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}会将太阳风层推向太阳的方向\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}pushes the heliosphere back towards the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.65,0:24:54.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果残骸的能量足够大\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If it's strong enough to push it
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.29,0:24:56.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就有可能会进入地球的轨道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all the way back to Earth's orbit,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:56.22,0:25:01.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的星球就会沐浴在具有辐射性的超新星残骸中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our planet gets a radioactive bath of supernova debris.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.29,0:25:04.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}好在这样的情况不常发生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Luckily, this doesn't happen very often.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.13,0:25:07.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}最后一次出现是在200万年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The last one was perhaps two million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.57,0:25:10.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}邻近的一颗恒星爆发了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A neighboring star explodes a million years
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.73,0:25:14.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球上还要再过100万年才会出现人类这个物种\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}before there's even such a thing as the human species.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.41,0:25:16.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们从何得知此事\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How can we possibly know this?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:16.91,0:25:19.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为死亡的恒星会留下踪迹\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Because the dying star left its traces
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.74,0:25:22.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就藏在海洋下几英里处\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}miles below the surface of the ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.25,0:25:26.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是锰结核 就像这块小石头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Manganese nodules, small rocks like this one,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.98,0:25:31.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它分散在深海的海床上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are scattered over much of the deep sea floor.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.49,0:25:34.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的生长速度非常缓慢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They grow very slowly.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.33,0:25:39.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}100万年才能长1毫米\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm talking a millimeter in a million years,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.10,0:25:43.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一层层的堆栈生长\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}layer upon layer.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.10,0:25:46.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}锰结核与细菌共生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These nodules grow in partnership with bacteria
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.17,0:25:51.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们吸取溶解在海水中的矿物质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by taking up minerals dissolved in the seawater.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:51.04,0:25:55.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}超新星会产生一种具有放射性的铁\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A supernova produces a radioactive form of iron,
Dialogue: 0,0:25:55.05,0:25:59.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它和地球上自然产生的任何一种物质都不一样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}unlike anything made by natural processes on Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.12,0:26:01.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}研究人员发现了这种铁的痕迹\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Researchers found telltale traces of this iron
Dialogue: 0,0:26:01.52,0:26:03.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就长在锰结核中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a thin layer below the surface
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.52,0:26:05.49,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}外壳下的一个浅层里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the manganese nodules.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:05.52,0:26:08.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}研究人员把已知的锰结核的生长速率\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They used the known rate of growth of the nodules
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.36,0:26:10.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和每层的生长时间联系起来\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to date that layer and to connect it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:10.69,0:26:14.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就能知道亿万年前恒星灭亡的命运了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to the fate of a star that perished eons ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.33,0:26:19.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你看到的是石头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The difference between seeing nothing but a pebble
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.24,0:26:23.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但在科学家眼里 这是深藏在里面的宇宙的历史\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and reading the history of the cosmos inscribed inside it
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.67,0:26:26.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是科学的力量\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is science.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.25,0:26:32.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}星际大洋黑暗而深远\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The interstellar ocean is dark and deep.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.25,0:26:36.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}从那里看 太阳只不过是天空中一颗最亮的恒星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Out here, the Sun is just the brightest star in the sky.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.25,0:26:39.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旅行者号依然保持着\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Yet the Voyagers maintain their regular communications
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.69,0:26:41.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与美国宇航局喷气推进实验室定期的联系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with NASA's Jet Propulsion Laboratory,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:41.86,0:26:44.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们的交流要经过1光时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}talking back and forth across the light-hours
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.50,0:26:47.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就是宇宙飞船与母港之间的距离\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that separate these ships from their home port.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:47.40,0:26:51.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}再没有人造的物体\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No other objects touched by human hands
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.24,0:26:54.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}曾如此冒险远离家园\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have ever ventured this far from home.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.88,0:27:02.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当这些飞船\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even after they lose their ability
Dialogue: 0,0:27:02.38,0:27:04.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}失去了与人类通讯的能力之后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to respond to our command,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.45,0:27:06.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旅行者号最后一个也是最长的一个任务\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the last and, by far, the longest phase
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.68,0:27:08.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就此拉开序幕\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the Voyager mission will begin.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.63,0:27:20.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}1979年 当旅行者号绕着木星旋转时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Back in 1979, when both Voyagers rounded Jupiter,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.83,0:27:23.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}木星的巨大引力就像一个弹弓\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}its massive gravity acted as a slingshot,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.26,0:27:25.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把它们抛出太阳系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}flinging them out of the solar system
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.27,0:27:27.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让它们得以在银河系的恒星间航行\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to travel among the stars of our galaxy
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.47,0:27:29.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}时间是10亿年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.94,0:27:32.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当年 卡尔?萨根意识到旅行者号的任务\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Carl Sagan recognized that the Voyager mission
Dialogue: 0,0:27:32.61,0:27:36.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}为人类提供了两张接近永恒的机票\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}offered two free tickets to something approaching eternity.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:36.68,0:27:39.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他组建了一个小队 创造了一些信息\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He assembled a small team to create a message
Dialogue: 0,0:27:39.68,0:27:42.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以便在未来的某一天\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to any civilization that might, one day,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.68,0:27:46.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当某个文明遇到这个废弃的航天器时可以读到它\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}encounter the derelict spacecraft.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:49.29,0:27:51.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}26个世纪前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}26 centuries ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:51.49,0:27:54.29,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}亚述国王艾萨克哈顿写道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Assyrian king Esarhaddon wrote...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.33,0:27:57.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}"朕以青铜铸碑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}"I had monuments made of bronze
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.10,0:27:59.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}铭文于泥版\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and inscriptions of baked clay.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.77,0:28:03.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}遗之于基石 传之于后世"\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I left them in the foundations for future times."
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.17,0:28:07.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些象形图形延续了这一古老的传统\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These hieroglyphics continue that ancient tradition.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:07.51,0:28:10.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们被刻印在盖子上 上面的信息被设计成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They are inscribed on the cover of a message designed
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.51,0:28:14.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}方便其它世界或后世的生物阅读\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to be read by the beings of other worlds and times.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.65,0:28:18.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们人类与外星文明之间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What could we possibly have in common
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.22,0:28:19.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有可能会有什么共同点呢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with an alien civilization
Dialogue: 0,0:28:19.69,0:28:22.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们会有自己与众不同的进化史\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with its own separate evolutionary history
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.39,0:28:24.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}甚至有可能比我们更先进\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and one so far advanced beyond us
Dialogue: 0,0:28:24.66,0:28:28.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}能自由遨游于星际空间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that they can patrol interstellar space?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.90,0:28:30.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但至少有一样东西\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}One thing at least,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.46,0:28:32.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是宇宙间通用的语言\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a universal language...
Dialogue: 0,0:28:32.23,0:28:34.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}science.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.07,0:28:37.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}引力的束缚是很难被打破的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It's hard to break the bonds of gravity.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.07,0:28:39.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想要在宇宙之海中畅游\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can only sail the cosmic seas
Dialogue: 0,0:28:39.34,0:28:42.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你必须通晓数学与物理\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if you speak mathematics and physics.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.71,0:28:45.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}氢是宇宙中最常见的元素\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hydrogen is the most common element in the universe.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:45.81,0:28:47.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}氢原子中的电子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The electron in a hydrogen atom
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.82,0:28:49.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在它的旋转方向上作翻转运动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}flips the direction of its spin
Dialogue: 0,0:28:49.65,0:28:51.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它的速率或频率是恒定的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at a constant rate, or frequency.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:51.65,0:28:55.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}氢原子就像是个迷你的天然时钟\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hydrogen atoms are like tiny natural clocks--
Dialogue: 0,0:28:55.66,0:28:58.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}滴…答…走动\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tick... tock.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.49,0:29:00.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这就意味着我们与外星人共同拥有\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Now we have a unit of time in common
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.69,0:29:02.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相同的一个时间单位\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}with the extraterrestrials.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.33,0:29:04.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}了解了这个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}This will come in handy when we get to the next level
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.23,0:29:05.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}再转到下一个信息时就好理解了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.83,0:29:08.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}下面的信息是指示出我们在宇宙中的位置\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Here's our return address in space.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.44,0:29:11.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}脉冲星是快速旋转的中子星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Pulsars are rapidly-spinning neutron stars
Dialogue: 0,0:29:11.27,0:29:14.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它们会发出定期爆发的无线电波\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that give off regular bursts of radio waves.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.41,0:29:17.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你可以根据这个来设定时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}You can set your clock by them.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:17.11,0:29:19.68,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}太阳位于这个示意图的中心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Sun is at the center of this diagram,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.71,0:29:23.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这些线条指向14颗最近的脉冲星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the lines point to the 14 nearest pulsars.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.38,0:29:27.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有一个简单的标签指示出了每颗脉冲星的特有频率\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A simple code labels each pulsar with its unique frequency,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.22,0:29:29.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}并用氢原子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}using the ticktock of the hydrogen atom
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.39,0:29:31.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}作为计时单位\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as the unit of time.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:31.13,0:29:33.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此 外星的天文学家能利用这张示意图\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}So alien astronomers could use this diagram
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.96,0:29:36.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}来定位出旅行者号航天器的母星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to locate the home star of the Voyager spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.56,0:29:38.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在我们银河系中的位置\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in our galaxy.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.20,0:29:39.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们还能知道\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They could also tell
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.80,0:29:41.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这艘航天器已经发射多久了\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how long ago the spacecraft was launched.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.87,0:29:44.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这一点很重要\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And that's important because the Voyager record
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.07,0:29:48.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为旅行者号的外壳设计寿命是10亿年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}has a projected shelf life of 1,000 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:51.11,0:29:52.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就想象一下你是一个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Become an extraterrestrial archaeologist
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.75,0:29:54.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}外星球的考古学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for a few moments.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.75,0:29:57.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有一架人造航天器完成了它在星际大洋中的使命\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}An artifact has been fished out of the interstellar ocean.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.09,0:30:00.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它是由外星智慧生命\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was made by beings
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.62,0:30:02.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在10亿年前建造的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that lived about a billion years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.79,0:30:04.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你要怎样通过它了解他们和他们的世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What would you make of them and their world?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.16,0:30:09.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们给我们送来了他们的音乐\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}They've sent us their music
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.90,0:30:13.97,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有用59种人类语言说出的问候方式\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and greetings in 59 human languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.87,0:30:20.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是地球上一位小孩子向你打招呼\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Hello from the children of planet Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.04,0:30:21.14,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}鲸鱼的语言\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And one whale language.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.14,0:30:26.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有一串声音的组合 包括土星五号火箭发射的声音\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And a sound essay that includes a Saturn V rocket launch.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.35,0:30:31.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一位母亲对她新生的婴儿说的话\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A mother's first words to her newborn baby.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.69,0:30:33.99,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}哦 来吧\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Oh, come on now.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:33.99,0:30:36.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}做个好孩子…做个好孩子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Be a good boy... be a good boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.16,0:30:38.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一位刚刚坠入爱河的年轻女子的脑波\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The brain waves of a young woman newly fallen in love.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:41.96,0:30:45.50,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有脉冲星的声音\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And the sound of a pulsar.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.64,0:30:54.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}所有这些都能存在10亿年之久\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}All of that will live for a billion years.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.02,0:31:10.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}10亿年有多久\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How long is a billion years?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:19.79,0:31:22.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果你能把创世大爆炸以来的时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you compress all the time since the Big Bang,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:23.03,0:31:25.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也就是宇宙诞生的那一刻开始的时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the explosive birth of the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.03,0:31:27.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}压缩成一个地球年的话\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}into a single Earth year,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.03,0:31:30.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}10亿年就相当于这1年中的1个月\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a billion years is about one month of that year.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.37,0:31:34.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}10亿年前的地球上发生了些什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}What was happening on Earth a billion years ago?
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.74,0:31:40.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}大部分的地球陆地都聚集在一个超大陆上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Most of Earth's land was amassed into a supercontinent
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.78,0:31:42.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们称之为罗迪尼亚大陆\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}called Rodinia.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.48,0:31:46.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是一个荒地 没有动物 没有植物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was a barren desert-- no animals, no plants.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.15,0:31:48.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}10亿年前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A billion years ago, there wasn't enough oxygen
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.12,0:31:50.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}空气里没有足够的氧以形成臭氧层\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in our atmosphere to form an ozone layer,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.56,0:31:53.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有它的保护\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and without it, ultraviolet radiation
Dialogue: 0,0:31:53.22,0:31:55.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}紫外线会阻止生命在陆地上生存\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}prevented life from colonizing the land.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.96,0:31:58.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}罗迪尼亚大陆看上去可能更像火星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Rodinia probably looked more like Mars
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.50,0:32:01.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而不像今天的地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than present-day Earth.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:01.23,0:32:03.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}巨大的海洋世界产生大暴雨\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The giant world ocean produced huge rainstorms
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.97,0:32:06.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}造成洪水和侵蚀\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}causing flooding and erosion.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.50,0:32:09.61,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}冰川形成 它们缓慢而无情的运动着\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Glaciers formed, and their slow but relentless movements
Dialogue: 0,0:32:09.64,0:32:12.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}把陆地塑造成新的样子\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}carved the land into new shapes.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.84,0:32:16.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}单细胞的生物主宰着海洋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Single-celled organisms dominated the oceans,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.25,0:32:19.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}被称为"微生物席"的生物集群地已经开始出现\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}but some existed in colonies called "microbial mats,"
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.85,0:32:24.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}第一个多细胞生物很快会演变形成\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the first multicellular organisms would soon evolve.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.59,0:32:26.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}10亿年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And a billion years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.59,0:32:28.56,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}今天的地球又会变成怎样…\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what will Earth be like...
Dialogue: 0,0:32:28.59,0:32:31.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的城市 埃及的金字塔\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}long after our cities, the Egyptian pyramids,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:31.26,0:32:34.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}洛基山脉 是否早已被侵蚀为尘土\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the Rocky Mountains have all been eroded to dust?
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.43,0:32:37.00,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对于这么久远的时间来说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There are few things we can say with confidence
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.04,0:32:40.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们没有几件事是可以说得清的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}about such a far distant time.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.71,0:32:46.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们唯一可以肯定的是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The only thing we can say for sure
Dialogue: 0,0:32:46.21,0:32:50.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们所认识的地球会发生巨变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is that Earth as we know it will be so changed
Dialogue: 0,0:32:50.05,0:32:53.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}几乎没有人会认得出 这曾经是我们的家园\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that we would scarcely recognize it as home.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.38,0:32:56.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但就算是10亿年后\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But even a thousand million years from now,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.95,0:33:00.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们人类的本性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}something of who we were and the music that we made
Dialogue: 0,0:33:00.49,0:33:02.76,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和我们在久远的春天写下的音乐\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in that long-ago spring...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.79,0:33:04.80,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都会延续下去\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}will live on.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.67,0:33:12.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在如此遥远的未来 我们的太阳系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In that distant future, our Sun will have completed
Dialogue: 0,0:33:12.87,0:33:16.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}完成了绕着银河系中心公转4圈的历程\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}another four orbits around the center of the galaxy...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.52,0:33:29.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旅行者号早已飞到了远离太阳的领域\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}...and the Voyagers will have ventured far from the Sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:32.36,0:33:35.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}卡尔?萨根曾是旅行者号影像小组的一员\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Carl Sagan was a member of Voyager's imaging team,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.09,0:33:39.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}旅行者号拍摄的最后一张照片来自于他的想法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and it was his idea that Voyager take one last picture.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.33,0:33:41.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在一代人以前\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}A generation before,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:41.37,0:33:44.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}阿波罗登月飞行的最后一位宇航员\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}an astronaut on the last Apollo flight to the Moon
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.24,0:33:46.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}照下了一张地球的全景照片\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}had taken a picture of the whole Earth--
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.90,0:33:50.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这是一个没有边界的行星\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the planet as a world without borders.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.11,0:33:53.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它成了一种新意识的象征\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It became an icon of a new consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.51,0:33:57.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}卡尔实现了这个过程的下一步\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Carl realized the next step in this process.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.68,0:34:00.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他说服了美国宇航局把旅行者一号的镜头\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}He convinced NASA to turn the Voyager 1 camera
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.75,0:34:04.52,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在飞过海王星时 转回地球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}back towards Earth when the spacecraft went beyond Neptune
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.56,0:34:08.19,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}让它最后看一眼家园 他所说的那个\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for one last look homeward at what he called...
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.23,0:34:11.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}泛着苍白蓝光的小点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the pale blue dot.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.04,0:34:18.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在那里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's here.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.64,0:34:20.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是家园\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's home.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.20,0:34:21.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那是我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's us.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.81,0:34:24.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在那里 你爱的每个人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}On it, everyone you love,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.54,0:34:26.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你认识的每个人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}everyone you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.58,0:34:28.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你听说过的每个人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}everyone you ever heard of,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.58,0:34:31.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这世上存在过的每个人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every human being who ever was,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.25,0:34:33.62,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}度过了自己的一生\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lived out their lives.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.65,0:34:37.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}聚集在这里的 是我们的欢乐和痛苦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The aggregate of our joy and suffering,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.42,0:34:40.22,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是成千上万的宗教信仰 意识形态\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}thousands of confident religions, ideologies,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.26,0:34:42.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}和经济学说\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and economic doctrines,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.26,0:34:44.39,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个猎手与觅食者\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every hunter and forager,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.43,0:34:46.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个英雄与懦夫\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every hero and coward,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:46.43,0:34:49.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个文明的创立者和毁灭者\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every creator and destroyer of civilization,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.90,0:34:51.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每个国王与农夫\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every king and peasant,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.90,0:34:53.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每对年轻的爱侣\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every young couple in love,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.94,0:34:57.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一个母亲与父亲 充满希望的孩子们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every mother and father, hopeful child,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.24,0:34:59.48,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}发明家与探险家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}inventor and explorer,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.51,0:35:03.15,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一位高尚的教师 每一位贪腐的政客\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every teacher of morals, every corrupt politician,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.18,0:35:07.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每一位超级明星 每一位最高领袖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every superstar, every supreme leader,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.29,0:35:11.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}人类史上的每一位圣人和罪人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every saint and sinner in the history of our species,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.16,0:35:13.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都生活在这里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}lived there...
Dialogue: 0,0:35:13.16,0:35:14.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如一粒微尘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on a mote of dust
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.99,0:35:18.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}悬浮在一束阳光之中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}suspended... in a sunbeam.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.26,0:35:22.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球是在浩瀚的宇宙背景下的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth is a very small stage
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.50,0:35:26.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}一个很小的舞台\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in a vast, cosmic arena.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:26.34,0:35:29.57,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想想过去的血流成河\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Think of the rivers of blood
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.61,0:35:33.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}那为帝王将相而流的血\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spilled by all those generals and emperors
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.34,0:35:35.78,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只为让他们在光荣和胜利中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}so that in glory and triumph
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.81,0:35:38.75,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}成为瞬间的伟人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they could become the momentary masters
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.78,0:35:42.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}占有那一个小点中…那一小部分\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of a fraction... of a dot.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:42.05,0:35:45.16,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}想想那无尽的残酷\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Think of the endless cruelties visited
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.19,0:35:48.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}图像里那一个像素点的某个角落的民众\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}by the inhabitants of one corner of this pixel
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.69,0:35:51.60,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}每天把这残酷施加到与他们没什么区别的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}on the scarcely distinguishable inhabitants
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.63,0:35:53.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}另一个角落的民众身上\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of some other corner.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.73,0:35:56.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们为何常常误解\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How frequent their misunderstandings,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.80,0:35:59.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们为何渴望杀死对方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how eager they are to kill one another,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.80,0:36:03.11,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们的憎恨为何如此狂热\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}how fervent their hatreds.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.14,0:36:05.64,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们在装模做样\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our posturings,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.68,0:36:08.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们自以为很重要\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}our imagined self-importance,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.75,0:36:11.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}妄想着我们人类地位特殊\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the delusion that we have some privileged position
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.35,0:36:12.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在宇宙中与众不同\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the universe,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.98,0:36:17.65,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这一切 都因这泛着苍白蓝光的小点而动摇\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}are challenged by this point of pale light.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.69,0:36:19.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的星球\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Our planet...
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.72,0:36:22.73,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不过是一粒孤独的微尘\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}is a lonely speck in the great,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.76,0:36:25.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}笼罩在伟大的宇宙黑暗之中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}enveloping cosmic dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.86,0:36:28.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们默默无闻\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}In our obscurity,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.70,0:36:31.47,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}沉浸在无尽的浩瀚里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in all this vastness,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.50,0:36:35.21,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有一丝线索显示 除了我们自己\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}there is no hint that help will come from elsewhere
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.24,0:36:38.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有谁能拯救我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to save us from ourselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.21,0:36:42.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}地球是目前已知唯一有生命的世界\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The Earth is the only world known so far to harbor life.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.45,0:36:44.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命再无其它去处\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There is nowhere else,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.45,0:36:46.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}至少在不久的将来 亦是如此\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}at least in the near future,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.45,0:36:49.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没有外星球 供人类迁移\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to which our species could migrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.29,0:36:52.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只可参观\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Visit, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.06,0:36:54.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不能定居\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Settle, not yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.29,0:36:56.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不管你喜欢与否\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Like it or not,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.36,0:37:00.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}现在 只有地球供我们立足\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}for the moment, the Earth is where we make our stand.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.93,0:37:04.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}据说研习天文 可以让人谦卑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It has been said that astronomy is a humbling
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.27,0:37:08.37,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}塑造人心 磨炼个性\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and character-building experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:08.41,0:37:10.87,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也许再没有更好的方法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}There is perhaps no better demonstration
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.91,0:37:13.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}能比这遥远的画面\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of the folly of human conceits
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.78,0:37:17.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}更好地显示出人类的自负与愚蠢\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}than this distant image.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.32,0:37:20.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对我而言 它强调了我们的责任\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}To me, it underscores our responsibility
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.92,0:37:23.59,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要对人更友善\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to deal more kindly with one another
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.62,0:37:26.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}懂得珍惜与爱护\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and to preserve and cherish
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.12,0:37:28.26,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这泛着苍白蓝光的小点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the pale blue dot,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.29,0:37:31.43,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是我们知道的唯一的家园\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the only home we've ever known.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.34,0:37:40.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们是如何\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How did we,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.34,0:37:42.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在这一粒微尘上居住的渺小生物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tiny creatures living on that speck of dust,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.74,0:37:46.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是如何千方百计地把宇宙飞船\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}ever manage to figure out how to send spacecraft
Dialogue: 0,0:37:46.08,0:37:48.88,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}送入银河的星星之间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}out among the stars of the Milky Way?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.91,0:37:53.28,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就在几百年前 也就是宇宙历中的几秒时间\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Only a few centuries ago, a mere second of cosmic time,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:53.32,0:37:55.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们尚不知道自己身在何方 时为何时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we knew nothing of where or when we were.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.95,0:37:58.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}对宇宙的其它部分一无所知\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Oblivious to the rest of the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.76,0:38:01.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们身居囚笼\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we inhabited a kind of prison--
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.36,0:38:03.33,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}活在自己的小宇宙里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}a tiny universe
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.36,0:38:06.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}困在坚壳之中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}bounded by a nutshell.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.97,0:38:13.24,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们是如何逃出囚笼\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}How did we escape from the prison?
Dialogue: 0,0:38:13.27,0:38:17.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}是因为世世代代探索者的不懈努力\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}It was the work of generations of searchers
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.21,0:38:21.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们发自内心地遵从5条简单规则\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}who took five simple rules to heart.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.95,0:38:26.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}质疑权威\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Question authority.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.95,0:38:30.25,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不轻信人言\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}No idea is true just because someone says so,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.29,0:38:31.96,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}包括自己在内\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}including me.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.96,0:38:34.79,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}独立思考\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Think for yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.23,0:38:40.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}自我质疑\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Question yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.57,0:38:45.20,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}不因自己想要相信 而相信任何事情\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Don't believe anything just because you want to.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.24,0:38:50.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}相信不代表能成为现实\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Believing something doesn't make it so.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:50.04,0:38:52.01,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}依靠观察与实验\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Test ideas by the evidence gained
Dialogue: 0,0:38:52.04,0:38:55.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以实证检验想法\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}from observation and experiment.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.75,0:38:59.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果自己喜欢的想法没有通过全面的检验\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If a favorite idea fails a well-designed test,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.15,0:39:01.32,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就是错的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}it's wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.35,0:39:02.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}乐观一点\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Get over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.99,0:39:07.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}遵循证据 无论它指向哪里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Follow the evidence, wherever it leads.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.43,0:39:12.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果没有证据 不妄下定论\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If you have no evidence, reserve judgment.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.86,0:39:15.90,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也许最重要的规则就是\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And perhaps the most important rule of all...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.93,0:39:17.67,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}要记住 你也会犯错\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Remember, you could be wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:17.70,0:39:20.40,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}即使是最优秀的科学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Even the best scientists
Dialogue: 0,0:39:20.44,0:39:22.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}也曾经在某些事情上犯错\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}have been wrong about some things.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.37,0:39:25.08,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}牛顿 爱因斯坦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Newton, Einstein,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:25.11,0:39:27.84,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}还有历史上每一位伟大的科学家\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and every other great scientist in history,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:27.88,0:39:30.35,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}他们都犯过错\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}they all made mistakes.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.38,0:39:33.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这很正常 是人都会犯错\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of course they did-- they were human.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:33.59,0:39:37.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学让我们不再欺骗自己\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Science is a way to keep from fooling ourselves...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.92,0:39:40.69,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}欺骗别人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and each other.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.73,0:39:43.06,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学家们有罪吗\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Have scientists known sin?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.23,0:39:47.70,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:47.73,0:39:50.07,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们曾滥用科学\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We have misused science, just as we have
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.10,0:39:53.34,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就像手边的工具一样随意使用\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}every other tool at our disposal,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.37,0:39:55.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因此我们不能把科学\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and that's why we can't afford
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.57,0:39:59.51,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}放在少数的掌权者手中\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}to leave it in the hands of a powerful few.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.54,0:40:02.45,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当科学更多的属于全人类时\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}The more science belongs to all of us,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.48,0:40:05.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}它就越不会被乱用\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the less likely it is to be misused.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:07.79,0:40:10.42,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}科学的价值能阻止\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}These values undermine the appeals
Dialogue: 0,0:40:10.46,0:40:12.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}狂热与无知\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}of fanaticism and ignorance
Dialogue: 0,0:40:12.76,0:40:14.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}毕竟\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and, after all,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.66,0:40:17.09,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙的大部分是黑暗的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}the universe is mostly dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.13,0:40:20.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}只有点点的星光点缀着\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}dotted by islands of light.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.40,0:40:24.03,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}了解了地球的年龄 恒星的距离\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Learning the age of the Earth or the distance to the stars
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.07,0:40:26.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命的演变\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}or how life evolves--
Dialogue: 0,0:40:26.07,0:40:28.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}这会让世界有什么区别\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}what difference does that make?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:28.34,0:40:31.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}嗯 这取决于\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Well, part of it depends on how big a universe
Dialogue: 0,0:40:31.08,0:40:32.94,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}你愿意生活在多大的宇宙里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}you're willing to live in.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.98,0:40:34.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}有些人喜欢小宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Some of us like it small.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:34.98,0:40:36.58,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}没关系\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}That's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.61,0:40:37.98,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}完全可以理解\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Understandable.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.02,0:40:39.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}但我喜欢大的宇宙\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}But I like it big.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:39.75,0:40:42.89,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当我把这一切放在我的心里 我的脑海里\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when I take all of this into my heart and my mind,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:42.92,0:40:44.82,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我会感到心情振奋\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I'm uplifted by it.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:44.86,0:40:48.63,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}当这种感觉涌起 我希望看到它是真实的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And when I have that feeling, I want to know that it's real,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.66,0:40:52.13,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而不仅仅是我脑海中的想象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}that it's not just something happening inside my own head,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:52.16,0:40:54.30,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为这就是真相\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}because it matters what's true,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.33,0:40:56.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}而我们的想象\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and our imagination is nothing
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.80,0:41:00.17,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}与自然中令人惊叹的现实相比 根本不算什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}compared with Nature's awesome reality.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.31,0:41:08.31,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我想要知道 在那黑暗的地方有什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I want to know what's in those dark places,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:08.35,0:41:12.05,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}在创世大爆炸之前发生了什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and what happened before the Big Bang.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:14.12,0:41:16.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我想要知道 在宇宙的视界之外是什么\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I want to know what lies beyond the cosmic horizon,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.99,0:41:19.86,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命又是如何起源的\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and how life began.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.89,0:41:22.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}宇宙中有没有个地方\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}Are there other places in the cosmos
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.39,0:41:26.36,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}物质和能量在那里被赋予\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}where matter and energy have become alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.40,0:41:28.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}生命和意识\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and aware?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:35.87,0:41:38.04,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我想要了解我们的先祖\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I want to know my ancestors--
Dialogue: 0,0:41:38.08,0:41:39.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}了解他们每一个人\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}all of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:39.58,0:41:41.81,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我想要成为一个美好而强大的联接\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I want to be a good, strong link
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.85,0:41:43.71,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}联系世世代代的人类\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the chain of generations.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.75,0:41:45.55,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我想要保护我的孩子们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}I want to protect my children
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.58,0:41:48.72,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}以及未来的子孙后代\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and the children of ages to come.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.75,0:41:51.92,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们 代表着宇宙在这个世界的耳目\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We, who embody the local eyes and ears
Dialogue: 0,0:41:51.96,0:41:54.66,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}代表着宇宙在这个世界的想法与情感\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}and thoughts and feelings of the cosmos,
Dialogue: 0,0:41:54.69,0:41:57.93,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们开始了解人类的起源\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}we've begun to learn the story of our origins--
Dialogue: 0,0:41:57.96,0:42:01.83,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}思考繁星的故事 物质的演化\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}star stuff contemplating the evolution of matter,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.87,0:42:05.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}追溯意识起源之前那条漫长的道路\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}tracing that long path by which it arrived at consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.57,0:42:08.54,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们与这个星球上的其它生物\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}We and the other living things on this planet
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.57,0:42:10.74,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}携带着宇宙进化的遗产\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}carry a legacy of cosmic evolution
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.78,0:42:13.18,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}逾越了数十亿年\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}spanning billions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:13.21,0:42:15.41,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果我们将这些知识铭记于心\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}If we take that knowledge to heart,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.45,0:42:18.95,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}如果我们了解并热爱大自然的本质\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}if we come to know and love nature as it really is,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.98,0:42:22.02,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的子孙们一定会记住我们\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}then we will surely be remembered by our descendants
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.05,0:42:25.12,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}因为我们是生命之链中美好而强大的一环\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}as good, strong links in the chain of life.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.16,0:42:28.46,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}我们的子孙们也会继续这神圣的探索\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}And our children will continue this sacred searching,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:28.49,0:42:32.23,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}薪火相传 不断开拓\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}seeing for us as we have seen for those who came before,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.26,0:42:35.53,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}就在这宇宙之中 发现我们做梦\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}discovering wonders yet undreamt of...
Dialogue: 0,0:42:35.57,0:42:37.77,chs&eng,,0,0,0,,{\blur3}都想不到的奇迹\N{\blur3}{\fnCronos Pro Subhead\fs14\1c&H3CF1F3&}in the cosmos.
